Variables

-containers for storing data.
-created the moment value assigned to it.
eg. x="hey
    print(x)

Naming

-must start with letter or underscore
-can't start with number
-is case-sensitive

Local variable : defined and designed inside the function and used and called inside it.

Global variable : defined and declared outsude the function. can be used by everone, inside and outside the function.


Data types

-classification or catagorization of data items.
-represents the kind of value that tells what operations can be performed on a particular data.
-are actual classes.
Include : integer, string, boolean, etc...
